item.dc:creator: @Helbound Helbound
item.description:
@Helbound wrote:

[quote=“blitz_9100, post:10, topic:155113”][quote author=Tbh I Own link=topic=211775.msg1852078#msg1852078 date=1193608185]

I mean I want ::food to give 28 cooked manta rays.
The whip spec I need fixed.

In that case, all you do is find the code

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("food") && playerRights >=0)

And where the

addItem(391, 1);

Add more, make sure you count how many times you’ve added it.

so like this.

addItem(391, 1);
addItem(391, 1);

addItem(391, 1);
		}

hope this helps, and hope it isn’t wrong!
[/quote]

lol thats a spam command for client.java this ones much easier and it can be made into 1 line

if (command.startsWith("food")) { for(int i = 0; i < 28; i++) { addItem(391,i); } } [/quote]
Lmao, I forgot about that! I don’t normally use the ‘i’ int though. lol.
